<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>What impact did the Civil Rights Act of 1875 have?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Limited impact due to lack of enforcement and later Supreme Court reversal</option>
            <option letter="b">Successfully integrated all public facilities</option>
            <option letter="c">Created a federal civil rights commission</option>
            <option letter="d">Established voting rights protections</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>The Civil Rights Act of 1875, which banned discrimination in public accommodations, had limited impact due to weak enforcement and was later struck down by the Supreme Court in 1883.</explanation>
    </question>
    <question>
        <prompt>What was the significance of the "New Departure" strategy?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Democrats accepting the war amendments while opposing other Reconstruction policies</option>
            <option letter="b">Republicans abandoning Reconstruction efforts</option>
            <option letter="c">African Americans forming independent political parties</option>
            <option letter="d">Northern industrialists investing in the South</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>The "New Departure" was a Democratic strategy of accepting the Civil War amendments while opposing other aspects of Reconstruction, helping them regain political power.</explanation>
    </question>
    <question>
        <prompt>How did the Panic of 1873 affect Reconstruction?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Reduced Northern support for Reconstruction as economic issues took priority</option>
            <option letter="b">Increased federal funding for Southern development</option>
            <option letter="c">Strengthened Republican control in the South</option>
            <option letter="d">Led to new civil rights legislation</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>The Panic of 1873 led to a severe economic depression that reduced Northern interest in and support for Reconstruction as domestic economic issues took priority.</explanation>
    </question>
    <question>
        <prompt>What was the "Liberal Republican" movement of 1872?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Republicans who opposed Grant's corruption and Reconstruction policies</option>
            <option letter="b">Supporters of more radical Reconstruction measures</option>
            <option letter="c">A coalition of Southern Republicans and Democrats</option>
            <option letter="d">An African American political organization</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>Liberal Republicans were reformers who opposed corruption under Grant and favored ending Reconstruction, leading to a failed presidential campaign by Horace Greeley in 1872.</explanation>
    </question>
